description:
&lt;p&gt;Sussex Community NHS Foundation Trust is looking for experienced drivers to work within its busy courier service, based in Brighton and visiting healthcare and other premises across West and East Sussex. Using a range of vehicles, you&#39;ll be providing essential services to our patients, colleagues and commercial partners, transporting post, pathology, pharmaceuticals and other items.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To do this you&#39;ll need to have a full current UK or EU driving licence with at least two years&#39; driving experience and no more than three penalty points. You&#39;ll be a good team player who is comfortable managing their own time and workload when away from base. You&#39;ll have excellent customer services skills, a basic understanding of IT and will be willing to work flexibly within a busy and frequently changing service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our services operate Monday to Friday, excluding bank holidays, and working hours may be between 7am and 7pm.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tim Brett-Logistics Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;tim.brett@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01273 265955&lt;/p&gt;
